                             Quotation v1.02
                             
                              Introduction
                              
   This is a small program that, like many others, will display a quote
when it is run. That is all that the program does. It's not much, but I
have looked for a program like this, and when I couldn't find one like I
wanted, so I wrote my own You may use it, or you may not.

NOTE: Searching for a quote can sometimes take time, as it searches 
      through most of the file.

@endnode
@node Instructions
@next Credits
@previous Introduction
                             Quotation v1.02
                             
                              Instructions
                              
   The instructions for this program are very simple. The program is a CLI
only program. to run, simply type:

     1> Quotation
     
and you will be given a quotation, chosen at random from a quotation file.
(I have included a Doctor Who Quotation file, as I like Doctor Who.)
The quotation file - Quotes.txt, must be kept in the S: directory. 

The Doctor Who quote file I have included is only an example file. It could
easily be made larger.

To edit, or create, a quotation file, edit the S:Quotes.txt file, using 
and editor. The file is a normal ASCII text file. The following guide
lines must be followed:

o At the top of the file is the number of lines in the file

o Between the number and the first line of the first is a '~' on its own
  line
  
o Each quote is separated by a '~' on its own line, and on the last line.
  Anything else on the line will mean that it is part of the quote

@endnode
